# 18. レンとMEIKOととっておき

MEIKO: Here's your coffee and cheesecake. Would you like milk and sugar?
Akito: Pass. I mean... No, thank you.
Len: I'll have a coffee too!
Miku: You need milk and sugar, right? Here you go.
Len: Hmph. I may need it now, but eventually I'll be able to drink it without any. Stop treating me like a kid, will you?
MEIKO: Hehe. Those two sure are lively. Is it a little too awkward to chat now?
Len: Hey, Akito. Did you and Toya have a fight?
Akito: Well... Not exactly.
Akito: Apparently, he just never thought of us as a unit.
Len: Hm? I don't really know what happened, but you sure look sad, Akito.
Akito: .....
Len: I have a friend who's really important to me, too. We're always together, and it's so much fun when we sing, but...
Len: We still fight sometimes, so I kind of understand.
Len: It always feels really lonely after you fight with someone close to you.
Akito: Yeah...
Akito: .....
Akito: I just don't get it...
Akito: How am I supposed to take it when he suddenly tells me our music has no meaning?
Akito: With him, even surpassing RAD WEEKEND is possible...
MEIKO: He must really be important to you.
MEIKO: .....
MEIKO: Hey, I have something reserved for just such an occasion. Care to try it?
Akito: What is it?
MEIKO: Here you go! Drink that, and you'll feel right as rain♪
Len: Um... MEIKO, isn't that a whiskey glass?
Akito: This definitely doesn't look like something you should be serving to a minor.
MEIKO: Don't worry about it! Just toss it back!
Akito: Toss it... Hm?
Akito: This smells like oolong tea. Why go to the trouble of making it look fancy with ice and a nice glass?
Akito: Are you trying to fool me or something?
MEIKO: It's strange, don't you think? Even the things right in front of us aren't always exactly what they seem.
Akito: Huh? What's that supposed to mean?
MEIKO: Perhaps what your friend said isn't the way he truly feels.
Akito: .....
Akito: Toya isn't the joking type, so I just assumed he meant exactly what he said...
Akito: But if he wasn't being honest with himself...
Akito: Damn it, I need to...
Akito: Huh? A call from Ken?
Akito: Hello, this is Akito. Is something wrong? It's not like you to call me.
Akito: Toya is at the restaurant?
Akito: I'll be right there! Would you stay on the line?!
Len: Akito, good luck!
Akito: Right. Oh...and, um...
Akito: Thanks all for the help.
An's Father: Sorry for the wait, Toya. Here's your usual blend.
Toya: Oh, but Ken... Today, I...
An's Father: You came to say goodbye, yeah? This one's on me. Consider it a thank you for all the times you've come in before.
Toya: Thank you very much.
An: Maybe we should step out for a bit, Kohane. It looks like he's got something important to talk about.
Kohane: B-But, he said he came to say goodbye. Does that mean...
Toya: Would you stay?
Kohane: What?
Toya: You two are part of the reason I was finally able to come to a decision.
Toya: And besides, I'd feel bad leaving with Azusawa still worried about me.
Kohane: Aoyagi...
Toya: Just promise you won't tell Akito. I don't want him to be disappointed in me.
Kohane: Um, okay.
Toya: Ken, you've probably already heard from Akito, but I decided to quit singing as a member of BAD DOGS.
Toya: Though for me and my music, BAD DOGS was everything. So, that's why today will be my last time coming here.
An's Father: ...I see.
An's Father: We'll miss you around here. And one less person for Akito to complain to means my job'll get that much harder.
Toya: My apologies...
An's Father: Heh. I'm just kidding.
Toya: Ken, please take care of Akito for me.
Toya: He's really serious about surpassing you and RAD WEEKEND. He has a tough road ahead of him though and there's plenty of competition...
Toya: I know I don't really have any right to ask this of you, though.
An's Father: Don't worry. You can count on me.
Toya: Thank you very much.
An's Father: Akito can be pretty stubborn, eh? Nothing can break him. But that's what makes him so interesting.
An's Father: In that regard, though, I think you two are a lot alike.
Toya: I'm afraid you're wrong...
Toya: I'm not like Akito. The only reason I'm here is because I was running away...
